ieser Studien kann schließlich gezeigt werden, dass Variation ein elementarer Bestandteil der Lehrwerke ist und die Mehrheit der Autoren in ihren Werken Normenpluralität abbilden.  aThis volume shines a light on the supposed tension between linguistic norm and variation in the early modern period by looking at early modern foreign language textbooks. Besides presenting the textbooks as sources, it is first and foremost about analyzing the authors’ ideas of norms and how they were implemented in language use. Studies of grammatical phenomena and language awareness open up new perspectives on linguistic norms and language use.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aFrühe Neuzeit. 4aHistorische Morphosyntax. 4aSprachnorm und Sprachgebrauch. 4aVariation. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / Historical & Comparative.2bisacsh  aEarly Modern Period.  aHistorical Morphosyntax.  aLanguage Norm.  aLanguage Use.  aVariation.1 aHübner, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2023z9783111318240oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831111691940 cprintz978311116857940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311116871540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111168715423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111168715/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-DSPb2023